= STAT 253/317: Syllabus

[https://congma1028.github.io/index.html Cong Ma], University of Chicago, Winter 2026

== Schedule


. Week 1: Foundations and Basic Examples
.. Jan 6 (Tue): Lecture 1 — Markov chains; transition probabilities; Chapman–Kolmogorov equations; n-step transitions; simple finite examples
.. Jan 8 (Thu): Lecture 2 — Communication classes; irreducibility; basic structure of state space; motivating examples (random walk, simple population models)
. Week 2: Stationary Distributions and Long-Run Behavior
.. Jan 13 (Tue): Lecture 3 — Stationary distributions (πP = π); examples; existence and intuition
.. Jan 15 (Thu): Lecture 4 — Long-run behavior: limiting distributions; ergodic theorem (conceptual); periodicity; when convergence occurs
. Week 3: Recurrence/Transience and Reversibility
.. Jan 20 (Tue): Lecture 5 — Recurrence vs. transience; positive recurrence; expected return times; examples (random walk, absorbing chains)
.. Jan 22 (Thu): Lecture 6 — Reversible chains; detailed balance; examples and applications (random walk on undirected graphs)
. Week 4 Random walk and braching processes
.. Jan 27 (Tue): Lecture 7 — Generating functions and branching processes
.. Jan 29 (Thu): Lecture 8 — More on branching processes
. Week 5
.. Feb 3 (Tue): Midterm Exam (covers Lectures 1–8)
.. Feb 5 (Thu): Lecture 9 — Counting process and Poisson process; exponential distribution
. Week 6
.. Feb 10 (Tue): Lecture 10 — Thinning, superposition, and related properties
.. Feb 12 (Thu): Lecture 11 — Continuous-time Markov chains: construction and holding times
. Week 7
.. Feb 17 (Tue): Lecture 12 — Generator matrices; Kolmogorov equations; examples
.. Feb 19 (Thu): Lecture 13 — Introduction to martingales; conditional expectation; simple examples
. Week 8
.. Feb 24 (Tue): Lecture 14 — Optional stopping (elementary cases): Gambler's ruin
.. Feb 26 (Thu): Lecture 15 — Brownian motion: definition, basic properties, scaling
. Week 9
.. Mar 3 (Tue): Lecture 16 — Brownian motion as a martingale; reflection principle (intro)
.. Mar 5 (Thu): Lecture 17 — Stopping times and hitting probabilities for Brownian motion